{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "vop", "internal": "glass", "icon": "VOP/glass", "version": null, "namespace": null}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Glass Shader"], "extent": [61, 78]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Simulates a translucent material such as glass, and returns the\ncombined color, opacity, and alpha."], "extent": [78, 186]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This operator simulates a translucent material such as glass, and\nreturns the combined color, opacity, and alpha."], "extent": [186, 301]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The index of refraction (", {"type": "code", "text": ["eta"]}, ") is the most important parameter because it\ncontrols the amount of the transmission (ie. refraction) of the surface.\nIts neutral value is 1. The environment color is ignored unless you\nspecify a valid environment map. The reflection bias is used to help\neliminate self-reflection, and is typically a small number."], "extent": [301, 647]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["In order to prevent the renderer from computing standard transparency\n(i.e. non-refracted transparency), as is the case with glass-like\nsurfaces, the opacity is set internally to 1 to make the surface\n", {"type": "q", "text": ["opaque"]}, "."], "extent": [647, 859]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["If the Position (", {"type": "code", "text": ["P"]}, ") input and the Normal (", {"type": "code", "text": ["N"]}, ") input are not connected,\nthe global variables by the same names will be used instead. Typically\nyou will use ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/restpos", "type": "link", "text": ["Rest Position"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/restpos"}, " or ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/uvspacechg", "type": "link", "text": ["UV Space Change"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/uvspacechg"}, " as inputs for ", {"type": "code", "text": ["P"]}, ", and\nwill not touch ", {"type": "code", "text": ["N"]}, " unless you want to apply additional displacement to\nthe glass surface using an operator such as ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/bumpnoise", "type": "link", "text": ["Bump Noise"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/bumpnoise"}, ". If you need need\nto access the global variables directly, they are available from the\n", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/global", "type": "link", "text": ["Global Variables"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/global"}, " operator."], "extent": [859, 1394]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["See ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/render/envmaps", "type": "link", "text": ["how to create an environment/reflection map"], "fullpath": "/render/envmaps"}, "."], "extent": [1394, 1462]}, {"level": 1, "id": "related", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [1462, 1471], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/brushedmetalshader", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/brushedmetalshader"}], "extent": [1471, 1504]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/carpaintshader", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/carpaintshader"}], "extent": [1504, 1532]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/principledshader", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/principledshader"}], "extent": [1532, 1562]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/surfacemodel", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/surfacemodel"}], "extent": [1562, 1588]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/layercomp", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/layercomp"}], "extent": [1588, 1611]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/layermix", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/layermix"}], "extent": [1611, 1633]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/layerpack", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/layerpack"}], "extent": [1633, 1656]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/layerunpack", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/layerunpack"}], "extent": [1656, 1681]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/setlayercomponent", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/setlayercomponent"}], "extent": [1681, 1712]}], "container": true}], "text": "Related"}], "title": ["Glass Shader"], "summary": ["Simulates a translucent material such as glass, and returns the\ncombined color, opacity, and alpha."]}